	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-21T10:31:52">Sports Direct International Plc is a United Kingdom-based holding company. The Company is a sports retailer engaged in retailing of sports and leisure clothing, footwear and equipment; wholesale distribution and sale of sports and leisure clothing, footwear and equipment under Company-owned or licensed brands, and licensing of its brands. It operates through three business segments: Sports Retail, Premium Lifestyle and Brands. Its Sports Retail segment includes the United Kingdom and international retail network of sports stores along with related Websites. Its Premium Lifestyle segment includes premium retail businesses, such as Cruise and Flannels. Its Brands segment includes the portfolio of internationally recognized brands, such as Everlast, Lonsdale and Dunlop. The Company offers its products under the brands, including Slazenger, Karrimor, Nike, Under Armour, Reebok, Puma, Kangol, No Fear and Firetrap. Its subsidiaries include Direct Fishing Limited and Campri Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-31T23:43:58">BRIEF: For the 26 weeks ended 25 October 2015, Sports Direct International Plc revenues remained flat at L1.43B. Net income increased 27% to L145.4M. Revenues reflect Brands segment increase of 10% to L112.5M, Sports Retail segment remaining flat at L1.23B, Retail Sales- Sports Retail remaining flat at L1.23B, also reflect Retail - Life style segment decrease of 12% to L87.7M, Retail Sales- Premium Lifestyle decrease of 12% to L87.7M.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
